        • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

          Roma's first XI personnel is as good as any team in Serie A which doesn't rhyme with Tuventus. N'Zonzi playing would allow the CBs to split wide and offer protection to the FBs and his passing ability is better than DdR so that decision should be relatively simple if you take sentiment out of the equation. EdF will need to persevere with a settled midfield otherwise there is little chance of his team hitting form. This means putting up with Pellegrini's dud games and Cristante's currently underwhelming performances for the long-term good. Chievo leak goals, so I expect Roma to score a few but I'm more concerned with the other side of the ball. This is probably a wildly optimistic prediction but here goes.... 4-0 Roma.
